trigger: When the user types /djt-test-coverage or /djt-test-coverage --apply, execute the appropriate phase of the test coverage workflow exactly as defined in SKILL.md. Phase 1 (audit) scans source files, detects the testing framework and its boundaries, evaluates coverage depth across categories A–G, and writes a prioritized checkbox report. Phase 2 (--apply) re-reads the populated report, implements only checked items, and commits on a dedicated branch.
notes: Always detect the testing framework first — its boundaries constrain what counts as a missing test. Never suggest tests for code outside the framework's testable surface. Do not implement anything until the user has checked boxes in the report and explicitly runs --apply.
